    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) in a bowl</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and stir it all together – this is your<strong> marinade</strong></p>",
